  "prompt": "How do you play the game Snaps?",
  "response": "Snaps is a word-guessing game where one player thinks of a famous person, and the other player tries to guess who it is by asking yes-or-no questions and receiving answers through snaps and verbal clues. Here's how to play:\n\n1. One player (the answerer) thinks of a famous person.\n\n2. The guesser asks yes-or-no questions to narrow down who the person might be.\n\n3. The answerer can only respond with:\n- Snaps (finger snapping)\n- Verbal responses like \"no\" or \"yes\"\n\n4. If a yes/no question can't be answered directly, the answerer must spell out the name using a special code:\n- Consonants are represented by the number of snaps corresponding to the letter's position in the alphabet\n- Vowels are represented by saying \"snap\" in a certain way\n\nFor example, if the name is \"Tom Hanks\":\n- T = 20 snaps\n- O = saying \"snap\" softly\n- M = 13 snaps\n- H = 8 snaps\n- A = saying \"snap\" with a rising tone\n- N = 14 snaps\n- K = 11 snaps\n- S = 19 snaps\n\nThe guesser tries to piece together the name based on the snaps and verbal clues.",
